{With 12 points and five ♠s, when SOUTH hears her partner open 1NT she knows

there is a game - either 3NT or 4♠.

SOUTH first transfers NORTH to ♠s, then jumps to 3NT, giving NORTH the choice.

NORTH has three ♠s, so he chooses 4♠, taking the 8-card Major fit.}
